profile:
Best Painters in the Fraser Valley!
 
Benchmark Painting is a family run business providing residential and commercial service to the entire Lower Mainland. Our team of professionals offer quality interior and exterior solutions for any project, large or small.  Benchmark Painting has earned and maintained an exceptional reputation by delivering exactly what our customers expect in a professional painting.

products:
Voted Best Painting Company 2010 by the consumers of Homestars.com!

Rooms starting at $99 each including all paint and labour. 3 room minimum required.  Call today for details.  
 
Call today for this promotion!
services:
Residential & Commercial Specialists
Benchmark Painting is committed to providing top quality workmanship as well as superior customer service. Benchmark's team of professionals offer quality interior and exterior solutions for any home or Business, both large and small. We offer free estimates and a limited one year warranty. 

Ceiling Re-Texturing
Has water or a renovation damaged your ceiling?
Benchmark painting is an industry leader in ceiling repair and re-texturing.

Surface Preparation
We never cut corners on surface preparation. We will sand, caulk, fill and prime all surfaces as needed. Thorough preparation is essential to quality painting. we will always apply two coats of paint. Your work will be done exactly as contracted and as scheduled. You can expect this and more from Benchmark Painting. 

Moulding Installations
Benchmark Painting Provides all your moulding needs with the attention to detail and quality our clients have come to expect from us.

profile:
“Why Master Painting”

Master Painting will orchestrate your project from beginning to end. Over the years they have refined their process down to an art form. From start to finish, their entire approach to job completion is client focused. The only thing that matters to Dave and Amy is your vision for your home and how they can achieve that vision

What You Get With Master Painting

Whole package bathroom, kitchen and whole home renovations – from estimate to final walkthrough
Guaranteed quoting system – barring any significant surprises we will not exceed the final written quote.
Seamless integration of design, cost and project management
Subcontractor relations – long standing working relationship with trades
In-house Interior designer – turn your dream kitchen into reality
Process education – a clear explanation of project cost, schedule
We return Your phone call – guaranteed within 24 hours on business days

Dave Waldner grew up in renovations. Throughout his childhood, the house’s he lived in were continually being remodelled, and when he was 10 years old, he started helping out his dad on his drywall crew. He began painting houses with his brother Jeremy at the age of 15, and within a month he was running a crew of his own.

In 2008 Dave and his wife Amy moved to Chilliwack, B.C. to start their business. Within a few years, they have established themselves as one of the most visible and highly rated painting and renovation companies in the eastern Fraser Valley.

There are 3 essential things to know about Dave Waldner: he loves his family, anything Star Wars related (look at his license plate), and building dream kitchens. In that order.

profile:
Rainforest Painting has been a recognized name in the Upper Fraser Valley for over 30 years.  
The company was owned by Len Schmidt until 2007 when he moved out of the Valley.  
The company was purchased by Bill Enns who was trained and worked with Len from 2001 - 2007.  

Bill has built his team to continue the tradition of quality workmanship and service the company has been known for.  
With Bill’s passing in December 2018, the company is now owned by his wife, Judy and his son Terry is now the General Manager of the company, taking care of the day to day operations of Rainforest Painting.  
Terry has worked by Bill’s side for the past 11 years and ran the company in the summer of 2018 when Bill fell ill.

The focus of Rainforest Painting has always been on quality workmanship and working with the client to achieve what they envision.  
We work closely with the client in colour choices, the best products suited for the job and efficient use of time in order to get the work done.

Whether we're painting one room for you or your entire home or business, we want to hear you say, "we just love how it all turned out!"

604-798-2900
INFO@RAINFORESTPAINTING.CA
